main event: A circular object was observed overhead at San Acacia Dam, N. Mex. in 1948 by USAF M/Sgts.
interesting points: The object was observed vertically overhead at an altitude of 20,000 feet.
The sighting was made by credible USAF M/Sgts.
The circular object was observed traveling at an unspecified speed in a northwest direction.
The report was documented on a temporary ATIC Form 329 in January 1952.
No photographs were present in the report.
